<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-188-598  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 188 598.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Feb 26 1990 n289 p60(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Export rules to soften. (the Coordinating Committee onMultilateral Export Controls considers easing restrictions ontrade with Eastern Europe)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Roussel, Anne-Marie.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Coordinating Committee on Multilateral Export Controls (COCOM)meets in Paris to discuss easing export restrictions ontelecommunications equipment to Eastern Europe and the SovietUnion.andP;  The Soviet Union would be subjected to stricter rules thanPoland, Hungary and other Warsaw Pact nations due to concerns overtechnology transfer issues.andP;  Telecommunications equipment vendorsare watching the deliberations carefully.andP;  US West Inc holds a$500 million contract to supply fiber optic technology to theSoviet Union.andP;  Other technology issues to be discussed includeAlcatel's tabled deal to provide an international gateway switchwith Signaling System 7 features to Poland, as well as X.25 packetswitching, which is now restricted for East European export.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   U S West Inc. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    USW.andO;Topic:     Coordinating Committee for Multilateral Export ControlsTelecommunicationsTechnology TransferEastern EuropeSoviet UnionCommunications EquipmentVendorsExport.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>